The paper deals with optimization problems over polymatroids, which are combinatorial structures commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also applies the results to non-cooperative polymatroid games, which falls under game theory (cs.GT). The use of convexity and regularity assumptions suggests a connection to convex optimization (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper also discusses the limitations of polymatroids as a maximal combinatorial structure, which could be relevant to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
